  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced", 
    "date": "1997-11-09", 
    "text": "Directs the Secretary of the Treasury to pay a specified amount to the survivors of 14 military personnel and one civilian who were killed on April 14, 1994, when U.S. F-15 fighter aircraft mistakenly shot down two UH-60 Black Hawk helicopters in Iraq. Limits attorney fees in connection with such survivor claims. Requires a report from the Secretary to the Congress on payments made."
